{
  "doc_id": "9283",
  "text": "Although many sexual minority individuals demonstrate resilience and effective coping strategies in the face of prejudice and do not evidence mental health disorders [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , for others, the consequences of living in an environment imbued with discrimination negatively affects psychological well-being and adaptation. I wrote the composite case study of Adam in order to explore the effects of sexual stigma on mental health and to provide corresponding treatment interventions for lesbian, gay, and bisexual (LGB) clients during the coming-out process. I sought to treat Adam within an integrative, flexible, and tailored framework by combining a cognitive-behavioral, clientcentered, and multicultural treatment approach. By demonstrating my first-hand clinical S.H. Hope Pragmatic Case Studies in Psychotherapy, http://pcsp.libraries.rutgers.edu Volume 10, Module 2, Article 5, experiences, the case study of Adam adds to the existing knowledge base of best treatment practices that are currently found within the psychological literature.",
